The paper deals with the problem of editing facial identity in videos using hand-drawn sketches. This involves 3D face model reconstruction and deformation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also proposes a real-time algorithm for this task, which involves machine learning and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of user intention recognition from input sketches, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method, which involves statistical learning (cs.LG).
